%2F64ece8263c42320019c03147%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222973%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJoe%20Biden%20walks%20with%20members%20of%20Culinary%20Workers%20Union%20Local%20226%20on%20a%20picket%20line%20outside%20of%20Palms%20Casino%20Resort%20on%20February%2019%2C%202020%2C%20in%20Las%20Vegas.%3Cp%3EMario%20Tama%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20new%20report%20from%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20looked%20at%20the%20economic%20impact%20of%20unions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%20union%20workers%20make%20more%20than%20their%20nonunion%20peers%20and%20have%20more%20benefits.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat%20might%20be%20a%20solution%20for%20a%20middle%20class%20dealing%20with%20rising%20debt%20and%20stagnant%20wages.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20middle%20class%20has%20been%20shrinking%20and%20weakening%20over%20the%20past%2050%20years.%20The%20Biden%20administration's%20latest%20research%20suggests%20that%20labor%20unions%20might%20be%20able%20to%20help%20turn%20that%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhome.treasury.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fjy1706%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Treasury%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20from%20the%20department%20to%20probe%20how%20unions%20impact%20the%20economy%20and%20middle%20class%20%E2%80%94%20looked%20at%20how%20the%20middle%20class%20has%20deteriorated%20in%20the%20US%20and%20ways%20that%20union%20benefits%20might%20ameliorate%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMiddle-class%20wages%20and%20household%20incomes%20have%20stagnated%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Janet%20Yellen%2C%20the%20Treasury%20secretary%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20call.%20%26quot%3BBoth%20renting%20and%20owning%20a%20home%20have%20become%20more%20expensive%20and%20so%20have%20education%20and%20healthcare.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiddle-class%20workers%2C%20whom%20the%20Treasury%20defines%20as%20falling%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20national%20income%20distribution%20and%20by%20markers%20such%20as%20owning%20a%20home%20or%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20college%20education%2C%20have%20seen%20real%20wages%20barely%20grow%2C%20income%20volatility%20increase%2C%20house%20prices%20skyrocket%2C%20and%20debt-to-income%20ratios%20more%20than%20double.%20Many%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaying-bills-credit-card-debt-student-loans-2023-8%5C%22%3Econtending%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20student-loan%20and%20mortgage%20debt%2C%20leaving%20them%20unable%20to%20save%20for%20retirement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decline%20in%20intergenerational%20mobility%20may%20be%20the%20single%20trend%20that%20best%20encapsulates%20the%20pervasive%20sense%20of%20the%20deterioration%20in%20the%20middle%20class%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Treasury%20report%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20unions%20can%20come%20in%2C%20Yellen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20findings%20challenge%20arguments%20that%20unions%20hold%20back%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Yellen%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnions%20could%20contribute%20to%20reversing%20the%20stark%20increase%20in%20inequality%20we've%20seen%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20promoting%20economy-wide%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%2050%20years%2C%20middle-class%20wages%20have%20stagnated%2C%20with%20middle-class%20workers%20still%20earning%20less%20than%20the%20highest%20earners'%20median%20income%20in%201970.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-middle-class-shrinks-as-richest-households-make-more-2022-4%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20share%20of%20adults%20living%20in%20middle-class%20households%20fell%20from%2061%25%20in%201971%20to%2050%25%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Treasury%20report%20found%20that%20union%20workers%20make%2010%25%20to%2015%25%20more%20than%20nonunionized%20colleagues.%20That's%20one%20economic%20factor%20that%20could%20give%20union%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20considered%20middle%20class%20%E2%80%94%20a%20boost.%20But%20beyond%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-in-union-make-1-million-dollars-more-over-lifetime-2022-10%5C%22%3Ehigher%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20union%20workers%20are%20five%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20what's%20called%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fgeneral%2Ftopic%2Fretirement%2Ftypesofplans%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520defined%2520benefit%2520plan%2520promises%2C%2524100%2520per%2520month%2520at%2520retirement.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefined-benefit%20retirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20that%20their%20retirement%20funds%20will%20guarantee%20a%20specific%20monthly%20payout%20once%20they're%20no%20longer%20working.%20Union%20workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20know%20their%20schedules%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20cutting%20down%20on%20scheduling%20instability%20and%20effectively%20putting%20more%20money%20in%20their%20pockets%20since%20they're%20able%20to%20plan%20ahead%20for%20things%20like%20childcare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnion%20workers%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20paid%20sick%20leave%2C%20medical%20benefits%2C%20subsidized%20commuting%2C%20and%20even%20more%20likely%20to%20receive%20unemployment%20insurance%20should%20they%20get%20laid%20off%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20report%20finds%20is%20%26quot%3Blikely%20the%20result%20of%20unions%20providing%20resources%20that%20ease%20filing%20procedures%20for%20members%20regarding%20their%20access%20to%20and%20eligibility%20for%20UI%20benefits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trickle-down%20effect%20of%20those%20benefits%20might%20boost%20the%20middle%20class%2C%20especially%20since%20nonunion%20firms%20feel%20a%20spillover%20effect%20and%20have%20to%20compete%20on%20workplace%20amenities%20and%20wages.%20The%20report%20found%20that%20the%20combination%20of%20higher%20union%20wages%2C%20stronger%20job%20security%2C%20and%20equity%20might%20help%20raise%20homeownership%20and%20education%20and%20spur%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20generations%2C%20union%20workers%20have%20fought%20for%20and%20won%20higher%20wages%2C%20better%20benefits%2C%20and%20safer%20working%20conditions%20for%20millions%20of%20American%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnion%20organizing%20and%20collective%20bargaining%20has%20made%20it%20possible%20for%20so%20many%20working%20families%20to%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20build%20a%20future%2C%20and%20retire%20with%20dignity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-union-approval-hasnt-been-this-high-since-1965-2022-8%5C%22%3Eincreased%20interest%20in%20labor%20unions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20prominent%20strikes%20across%20the%20country%2C%20union%20membership%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-union-membership-fell-lowest-rate-record-2022-2023-1%5C%22%3Estill%20remains%20at%20historic%20lows%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Labor%20advocates%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Funequalpower%2Fpublications%2Fprivate-sector-unions-corporate-legal-erosion%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20membership%20would%20be%20bolstered%20by%20stronger%20federal%20protections%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fpublication%2Fwhy-workers-need-the-pro-act-fact-sheet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estalled%20PRO%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bill%20that's%20unlikely%20to%20get%20passed%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-class-workers-falling-behind-unions-could-hel