aption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERedlining%20refers%20to%20a%20discriminatory%20housing%20practice.%20In%20the%20early%2020th%20century%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20created%20maps%20marking%20each%20area%20of%20the%20city%20with%20one%20of%20four%20classifications.%20Red%2C%20the%20lowest%20tier%2C%20was%20deemed%20%26quot%3Bhazardous.%26quot%3B%20It%20was%20also%20the%20only%20place%20Black%20people%20were%20allowed%20to%20purchase%20housing%20in%20the%20city.%20These%20formerly%20redlined%20areas%20still%20experience%20an%20outsize%20share%20of%20hazardous%20environmental%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20always%20communities%20of%20color%20facing%20the%20brunt%2C%26quot%3B%20Tee%20McClenty%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20at%20MN350%2C%20a%20grassroots%20organization%20in%20Minneapolis%20advancing%20climate%20policy%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20see%20communities%20of%20color%20%E2%80%94%20Black%20and%20brown%20like%20me%20%E2%80%94%20have%20a%20seat%20at%20the%20table%20to%20talk%20about%20what%20are%20the%20plans%20to%20improve%20the%20lives%20of%20those%20most%20impacted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMN350%20and%20other%20local%20environmental%20advocacy%20groups%20have%20pushed%20the%20city%20to%20address%20this%20discrepancy%20before%20it%20leads%20to%20a%20larger%20climate%20disaster.%20Last%20month%2C%20the%20city%20revised%20its%202013%20Climate%20Plan%2C%20laying%20out%20a%20comprehensive%20timeline%2C%20union%20protections%20for%20jobs%20created%20under%20the%20plan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20higher%20annual%20funding%20threshold.%20The%20new%20plan%20also%20emphasizes%20racial-equity%20provisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22848%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hotels%20and%20cafes%20in%20Gateway%20District%2C%20Minneapolis%2C%20Minnesota%2C%201939%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e79385a7adf7001907492f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22636%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHotels%20and%20caf%C3%A9s%20in%20the%20Gateway%20District%20in%20Minneapolis%20in%201939.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Vachon%2FLibrary%20of%20Congress%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20history%20of%20restrictive%20housing%20practices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201930s%2C%20President%20Franklin%20D.%20Roosevelt's%20New%20Deal%20hoped%20to%20stimulate%20the%20economy%20through%20homeownership.%20These%20programs%2C%20however%2C%20offered%20federal%20aid%20only%20to%20white%20Americans.%20The%20Home%20Owners'%20Loan%20Corporation%20created%20maps%20of%20major%20US%20cities%20that%20classified%20areas%20by%20risk-based%20characteristics%20to%20help%20banks%20determine%20how%20different%20properties%20should%20be%20valued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20existing%20racial%20makeup%20of%20neighborhoods%20often%20played%20an%20explicit%20factor%20in%20the%20classifications.%20Neighborhoods%20that%20had%20Black%20or%20Asian%20populations%20were%20considered%20less%20desirable%20and%20were%20redlined.%20The%20areas%20with%20the%20highest%20grades%20were%20given%20to%20rich%2C%20white%20neighborhoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERacist%20housing%20restrictions%20also%20guaranteed%20that%20houses%20would%20be%20bought%20only%20by%20white%20owners.%20Contractual%20agreements%20known%20as%20racial%20covenants%20would%20prohibit%20homes%20from%20being%20bought%20by%20particular%20groups%20of%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20early%20housing%20covenant%2C%20from%201910%20in%20Minneapolis%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmappingprejudice.umn.edu%2Fracial-covenants%2Fwhat-is-a-covenant%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20area%20%26quot%3Bshall%20not%20at%20any%20time%20be%20conveyed%2C%20mortgaged%20or%20leased%20to%20any%20person%20or%20persons%20of%20Chinese%2C%20Japanese%2C%20Moorish%2C%20Turkish%2C%20Negro%2C%20Mongolian%20or%20African%20blood%20or%20descent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224796%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20towards%20City%20Hall%2C%20Minneapolis%2C%20Minnesota%2C%20April%206%2C%201934.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e796c3a7adf70019074d69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223597%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeople%20marching%20toward%20City%20Hall%20in%20Minneapolis%20in%201934.%3Cp%3EAnthony%20Potter%20Collection%2FArchive%20Photos%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20people%20had%20begun%20to%20come%20to%20Minneapolis%20in%20the%20early%2020th%20century%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Flong-lasting-legacy-great-migration-180960118%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreat%20Migration%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20were%20quickly%20pushed%20into%20these%20redlined%20areas.%20Because%20of%20this%2C%20Black%20residents%20at%20the%20time%20primarily%20resided%20in%20the%20north%20side%20and%20in%20certain%20pockets%20of%20the%20south%20side%20of%20the%20city%2C%20reinforcing%20housing%20segregation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20north%20and%20south%20sides%20are%20cut%20off%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20downtown%20area%20by%20major%20highways%20and%20interstates.%20In%201960%2C%20the%20neighborhoods%20where%20highways%20were%20routed%20were%20home%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fminneapolis2040.com%2Fpolicies%2Ffreeway-remediation%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E82%25%20of%20the%20city's%20Black%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20has%20resulted%20in%20higher%20rates%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.minnpost.com%2Frace-health-equity%2F2023%2F02%2Fblack-minnesotans-disproportionately-affected-by-environmental-pollutants%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolluted%20air%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20water%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.health.state.mn.us%2Fdiseases%2Fasthma%2Fabout%2Fdocuments%2Fmnasthmaframework.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easthma%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20those%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndustrial%20manufacturing%20and%20chemical%20plants%20were%20also%20built%20in%20those%20areas%2C%20which%20also%20tended%20to%20lack%20tree%20canopies%20and%20green%20spaces.%20Neighborhoods%20with%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20low-income%20residents%20of%20color%20are%20over%20twice%20as%20likely%20to%20not%20have%20the%20appropriate%20number%20of%20tree%20canopies%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.startribune.com%2Ftree-cover-inequality-bipoc-neighborhoods-minneapolis-tornado%2F600202661%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStar%20Tribune%3C%2Fa%3E%20investigation%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%20there's%20not%20enough%20tree%20canopy%20in%20northern%20Minneapolis%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20is%20the%20hottest%20part%20of%20the%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20Ulla%20Nilsen%2C%20a%20senior%20organizer%20at%20MN350%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BLow-income%20and%20communities%20of%20color%20tend%20to%20not%20have%20as%20much%20access%20to%20air%20conditioning%2C%20substandard%20housing%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20well%20insulated%2C%20so%20it%20lets%20the%20heat%20through.%20Across%20the%20country%2C%20Black%20Americans%20are%20the%20most%20at%20risk%20for%20heat-related%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kff.org%2Fpolicy-watch%2Fextreme-heat-racial-health-equity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eillness%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20previously%20redlined%20neighborhoods%20suffer%20from%20extreme%20heat.%20Extreme%20heat%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fdo-not-get-yourself-killed-take-the-extreme-heat-seriously-2023-7%5C%22%3Edeadly%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20heat%20waves%20continue%20to%20intensify%20around%20the%20world%20during%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20A%20lack%20of%20tree%20canopies%20and%20green%20spaces%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20highways%20and%20industrial%20manufacturing%20plants%2C%20paved%20surfaces%2C%20and%20income%20inequality%20have%20all%20created%20a%20climate%20crisis%20for%20communities%20of%20color%20in%20Minneapolis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222219%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20coordinator%20gathers%20children%20in%20Minneapolis%20to%20attend%20summer%20activities.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e7986da7adf70019074f55%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20coordinator%20gathering%20children%20in%20Minneapolis%20to%20attend%20summer%20activities.%3Cp%3EDarlene%20Pfister%2FStar%20Tribune%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20flawed%20Climate%20Action%20Plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20the%20city%20adopted%20a%2047-page%20environmental%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flims.minneapolismn.gov%2FDownload%2FFile%2F2045%2FClimate%2520Action%2520Plan.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroad%20map%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20had%20high%20ambitions%20to%20achieve%20net-zero%20greenhouse-gas%20emissions%20by%202050.%20Called%20the%20Minneapolis%20Climate%20Action%20Plan%2C%20it%20sought%20to%20achieve%20that%20objective%20through%20energy-efficient%20homes%20and%20businesses%2C%20affordable%20carbon-free%20buildings%2C%2010%25%20of%20electricity%20from%20local%20renewable%20resources%2C%20grants%20for%20small%20businesses%20working%20toward%20the%20plan's%20objectives%2C%20and%20new%20green%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrganizers%2C%20however%2C%20say%20there%20was%20a%20major%20problem.%20The%20plan%20didn't%20detail%20a%20timeline%2C%20funding%20streams%2C%20or%20labor%20protections%20for%20jobs%20created%20by%20the%20plan.%20Nilsen%20also%20wanted%20the%20city%20to%20ensure%20those%20jobs%20would%20be%20accessible%20to%20lower-income%2C%20undocumented%2C%20and%20formerly%20incarcerated%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20outcry%20from%20activists%2C%20the%20city%20council%20submitted%20a%20new%20draft%20of%20a%2010-year%20plan%2C%20titled%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.minneapolismn.gov%2Fmedia%2Fcontent-assets%2Fwww2-documents%2Fgovernment%2F2023-Climate-Equity-Plan.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMinneapolis%20Climate%20Equity%20Plan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20soliciting%20public%20comments.%20The%20new%20plan%20put%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.minneapolismn.gov%2Fmedia%2Fcontent-assets%2Fwww2-documents%2Fgovernment%2FClimate-Equity-Plan-executive-summary-in-English.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eenvironmental%20justice%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20forefront%3B%20in%20a%20letter%20that%20introduces%20the%20document%2C%20Mayor%20Jacob%20Frey%20wrote%20that%20the%20new%20plan%20%26quot%3Bis%20about%20prioritizing%20low%20income%20and%20BIPOC%20communities%20first.%26quot%3B%20MN350%20launched%20its%20own%20campaign%2C%20ensuring%20that%20community%20members%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20give%20their%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20more%20than%20800%20people%20that%20submitted%20comments%2C%26quot%3B%20Nilsen%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20city%20listened%20to%20the%20comments.%20They%20didn't%20fix%20every%20single%20thing%2C%20but%20the%20plan%20was%20greatly%20improved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20plan%20includes%20a%20comprehensive%20timeline%2C%20union%20protections%20for%20new%20jobs%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%248%20million%20to%20%2410%20million%20in%20annual%20funding.%20Nilsen%20said%20they%20were%20also%20able%20to%20include%20explicit%20language%20guaranteeing%20that%20the%20city%20wouldn't%20add%20an%20additional%20tax%20burden%20on%20lower-income%20residents%20to%20make%20up%20for%