g%20federal%20tarmac%20delay%20rules.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20agency%20said%2043%20American%20flights%20had%20tarmac%20delays%20of%20over%203%20hours%20from%202018%20to%202021.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20Airlines%20was%20fined%20%244.1%20million%20for%20violating%20federal%20laws%20that%20prohibit%20airlines%20from%20keeping%20domestic%20flights%20on%20the%20tarmac%20for%20more%20than%20three%20hours%20without%20giving%20passengers%20the%20opportunity%20to%20deplane%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20said%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20largest%20fine%20an%20airline%20has%20ever%20been%20issued%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-fine-tarmac-delays-transportation-department-planes-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etarmac%20delay%20violations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20DOT%20said.%20The%20move%20is%20part%20of%20the%20agency's%20recent%20push%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdot-airline-customer-service-dashboard-shows-cancellation-delay-policies-meals-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eairline%20passenger%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20the%20issue%20is%20extreme%20tarmac%20delays%20or%20problems%20getting%20refunds%2C%20DOT%20will%20continue%20to%20protect%20consumers%20and%20hold%20airlines%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20Transportation%20Secretary%20Pete%20Buttigieg%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20half%20of%20the%20%244.1%20million%20fine%20will%20be%20used%20to%20compensate%20affected%20passengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202018%20and%202021%2C%20a%20total%20of%2043%20domestic%20American%20Airlines%20flights%20sat%20on%20the%20tarmac%20for%20more%20than%20three%20hours%2C%20impacting%205%2C821%20passengers%2C%20an%20investigation%20by%20the%20DOT's%20Office%20of%20Aviation%20Consumer%20Protection%20(OACP)%20found.%C2%A0On%20one%20of%20the%20flights%2C%20the%20airline%20did%20n