t%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173420%2FIMG_4411-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173420%2FIMG_4411-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670304%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20sapphire%20mines%20are%20located%20in%20the%20high-altitude%20mountains%20(seen%20snowcapped%20in%20the%20background)%20where%20weather%20conditions%20are%20very%20harsh.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20price%20of%20sapphire%20with%20a%20velvety%20texture%20and%20true-blue%20peacock%20colour%2C%20which%20is%20found%20only%20in%20Kishtwar%2C%20can%20reach%20Rs%205%2C00%2C000%20per%20carat.%20The%20precious%20stone%20can%20change%20the%20socio-economic%20landscape%20of%20Kishtwar%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20economically%20most%20underdeveloped%20and%20backward%20districts%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDevelopmental%20needs%20of%20Kishtwar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20literacy%20rate%20in%20Kishtwar%20at%2086.07%25%20is%20higher%20as%20compared%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20which%20stands%20at%2067.16%25%2C%20according%20to%20Census%202011.%20The%20mountainous%20district%20has%20also%20emerged%20as%20a%20power%20hub%20of%20North%20India%20with%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20functional%20and%20upcoming%20hydropower%20projects%20with%20a%20cumulative%20capacity%20of%206000%20MW%20clean%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Kishtwar%20faces%20acute%20deficiencies%20in%20providing%20basic%20civic%20amenities%20like%20road%20connectivity%20and%20healthcare.%20Industries%20are%20non-existent%2C%20and%20according%20to%20an%20official%20report%2C%20Kishtwar%20figures%20at%20the%20bottom%20among%20J%26amp%3BK%20districts%20in%20terms%20of%20improvements%20registered%20by%20the%20Commerce%20and%20Industry%2C%20and%20Environment%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKishtwar%20also%20lags%20at%2017%20out%20of%2020%20J%26amp%3BK%20districts%20in%20terms%20of%20human%20resource%20development%2C%2015%20in%20terms%20of%20public%20health%20sector%2C%20and%2016%20in%20terms%20of%20public%20infrastructure%20and%20utilities%20sector%20ranking%2C%20making%20it%20one%20of%20the%20most%20unliveable%20districts%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20despite%20being%20abundant%20in%20natural%20resources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28174023%2FIMG_4345.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28174023%2FIMG_4345.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28174023%2FIMG_4345-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28174023%2FIMG_4345-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670309%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20playground%20in%20Gulabgarh%20which%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20helipad%20for%20the%20ongoing%20Machail%20Yatra%2C%20a%20sacred%20Hindu%20pilgrimage%20held%20annually%20in%20Kishtwar.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSapphires%20have%20been%20mined%20by%20both%20the%20government%20and%20locals%20of%20Kishtwar%20since%201885%20when%20J%26amp%3BK%20was%20under%20the%20Dogra%20rule.%20But%2C%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20translated%20into%20any%20developmental%20benefits%20for%20Kishtwar%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Amar%20Singh%2C%20a%20Congress%20leader%20and%20ex-Sarpanch%20of%20Gulabgarh%20in%20Kishtwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20shown%20%E2%80%9Ckeen%20interest%E2%80%9D%20in%20exploring%20the%20sapphire%20wealth%20of%20Kishtwar%2C%20according%20to%20an%20official%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20Geological%20Survey%20of%20India%20along%20with%20officials%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20completed%20the%20preliminary%20survey%20of%20sapphire%20mines%20in%20Padder%20Valley%20and%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomprehensive%20strategy%E2%80%9D%20was%20formulated%20for%20%E2%80%9Cscientific%20exploration%E2%80%9D%20of%20sapphires.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%20this%20year%2C%20a%20team%20of%20geologists%20from%20Mineral%20Exploration%20and%20Consultancy%20Limited%20(MECL)%20along%20with%20the%20officials%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Geology%20and%20Mining%20Department%20left%20Kishtwar%20for%20a%20two-month%20expedition%20to%20explore%20sapphire%20mines%20in%20the%20high%20mountains%20of%20Padder%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDurgesh%20Devarshee%2C%20a%20MECL%20geologist%2C%20said%20that%20the%20team%20will%20set%20up%20a%20base%20in%20Padder%20Valley%20and%20carry%20out%20the%20G3%20stage%20of%20exploration%20involving%20geochemical%20and%20geological%20prospecting%20of%20the%20sapphire%20mines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20hopeful%20of%20taking%20the%20process%20to%20the%20G2%20stage%20which%20will%20be%20followed%20by%20G1%20stage%20when%20the%20estimate%20of%20sapphire%20in%20Kishtwar%20will%20be%20prepared%20and%20mining%20will%20hopefully%20commence%2C%E2%80%9D%20Devarshee%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Gulabgarh%20town%2C%20from%20where%20the%20team%20departed%20for%20Padder%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20challenges%20thrown%20by%20nature%20in%20reaching%20the%20high-altitude%20mines%2C%20and%20the%20difficulties%20faced%20by%20the%20workers%20and%20engineers%20in%20adjusting%20to%20the%20tough%20living%20conditions%20there%2C%20have%20so%20far%20hampered%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20explore%20the%20mines%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammad%20Shafi%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20Kijaie%20village%2C%20said%20that%20the%20journey%20to%20the%20sapphire%20mines%20is%20a%2040%20km%2C%20two-day%2C%20back-breaking%20hike%20from%20Gulabgarh%20through%20difficult%20mountain%20passes%20which%20ends%20at%20Sumcham%20village%20of%20Machail%20in%20Padder%20Valley.%20Mules%20are%20used%20for%20ferrying%20essentials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173834%2FIMG_4364.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173834%2FIMG_4364.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173834%2FIMG_4364-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173834%2FIMG_4364-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670307%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMohammad%20Shafi%20has%20worked%20in%20the%20sapphire%20mines%20of%20Kishtwar%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20but%20ailing%20health%20forced%20him%20to%20drop%20out.%20Photo%3A%20Jehangir%20Ali.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20mobile%20phone%20connectivity.%20Two%20to%20three%20camps%20are%20set%20up%20along%20the%20route%20from%20Machail%20around%20Bilakoth%2C%20Dangail%2C%20and%20Kundail%20for%20night%20shelters%20and%20stocking%20of%20essentials.%20Mules%20can%E2%80%99t%20stay%20at%20Bilakoth%20for%20the%20night%20and%20they%20have%20to%20be%20brought%20down%20to%20Dangail%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shafi%2C%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20sapphire%20mines%20from%201998%20to%202013%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbbas%2C%20a%20former%20sapphire%20mine%20worker%2C%20said%20that%20the%20weather%20vagaries%20restrict%20the%20mining%20season%20to%20just%20two%20months%20in%20a%20year%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20used%20to%20join%20the%20sapphire%20hunt%2C%20around%20a%20dozen%20labourers%20and%20their%20mules%20were%20selected%20by%20the%20government%20after%20police%20verification.%20Each%20labourer%20was%20paid%20Rs%20150%20per%20day%20while%20a%20mule%20earned%20Rs%201%2C000.%20We%20found%20a%20lot%20of%20sapphire%20stones%20but%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20benefit%20Kishtwar%20or%20its%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20lieutenant%20governor%20Manoj%20Sinha%20visited%20Kishtwar%20on%20Friday%2C%20August%2018.%20According%20to%20an%20official%20spokesperson%2C%20Sinha%20%E2%80%9Cexpressed%20gratitude%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20for%20%E2%80%9Cextending%20the%20support%20for%20survey%20and%20geological%20studies%20of%20sapphire%20mines%E2%80%9D%20in%20Kishtwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20next%20one%20year%2C%20we%20will%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20auction%20the%20sapphire%20mines%20in%20a%20scientific%20way%20that%20will%20give%20a%20boost%20to%20the%20local%20economy%20and%20it%20will%20also%20become%20one%20of%20the%20major%20contributors%20of%20(sic)%20growth%20of%20Jammu%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sinha%20said%20in%20an%20address%20to%20Panchayat%20representatives%20and%20residents%20of%20Kishtwar%20at%20Gulabgarh%2C%20according%20to%20the%20official%20spokesperson.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeputy%20commissioner%20Kishtwar%2C%20Dr.%20Devansh%20Yadav%2C%20said%20that%20the%20official%20team%20is%20expected%20to%20return%20from%20the%20Machail%20area%20of%20Padder%20Valley%20by%20next%20month.%20%E2%80%9COnce%20the%20auction%20process%20is%20started%2C%20we%20will%20ensure%20that%20Kishtwar%20gets%20good%20royalty%20from%20the%20sapphires%20which%20will%20be%20used%20for%20infrastructure%20development%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResidents%20of%20Kishtwar%20are%2C%20however%2C%20not%20so%20upbeat%20about%20the%20prospects%20of%20sapphire%20mining.%20Amar%20Singh%2C%20an%20activist%20and%20a%20resident%20of%20Gulabgarh%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20the%20government%20has%20ignored%20the%20developmental%20needs%20of%20Kishtwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPatients%20in%20Kishtwar%20are%20forced%20to%20visit%20Jammu%20or%20Srinagar%20for%20basic%20medical%20examinations%20such%20as%20an%20MRI%20scan.%20Most%20medical%20emergencies%20are%20referred%20to%20hospitals%20outside%20the%20district.%20Kishtwar%20is%20the%20most%20resourceful%20district%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20but%20the%20people%20here%20have%20been%20deprived%20of%20their%20benefits%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdul%20Majid%20Bichoo%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20Senior%20Citizens%20Forum%20in%20Kishtwar%2C%20said%20that%20the%20government%20must%20use%20the%20resources%20of%20Kishtwar%20to%20improve%20the%20public%20infrastructure%20like%20roads%20and%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20resources%20of%20Kishtwar%20should%20be%20invested%20in%20Kishtwar%20first.%20We%20have%20already%20been%20deprived%20of%20the%20benefits%20of%20power%20projects.%20If%20sapphire%20mining%20goes%20the%20same%20way%20and%20contracts%20are%20handed%20to%20outsiders%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20loss%20for%20Kishtwar%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20is%20the%20first%20in%20the%20four-part%20article%20series.%20The%20others%20will%20follow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693234838000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28173252%2FIMG_4426.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fjk-will-the-renewed-hunt-for-sapphires-aid-the-devlopment-of-neglected-kishtwar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20vast%20stretch