le%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Decoding%20PM%20Modi's%20Remarks%20On%20China%20And%20Supply%20Chain%20Worries%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20addressed%20the%20B20%20Summit%20India%202023%20on%20Sunday%20and%2C%20without%20naming%20China%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20profitable%20market%20can%20be%20sustained%20when%20there%20is%20a%20balance%20in%20the%20interests%20of%20producers%20and%20consumers.%20This%20also%20applies%20to%20nations.%20Treating%20other%20countries%20only%20as%20a%20market%20will%20never%20work.%20It%20will%20harm%20even%20the%20producing%20countries%20sooner%20or%20later.%20Making%20everyone%20equal%20partners%20in%20progress%20is%20the%20way%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20meet%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20also%20took%20a%20dig%20at%20China%20underlining%20its%20lending%20'policies'%2C%20which%20had%20reduced%20the%20Global%20South%20to%20being%20a%20consumer%20rather%20than%20a%20producer%20and%20saddled%20them%20with%20unviable%20debt%20that%20had%20resulted%20from%20China's%20%26quot%3Bopaque%20initiatives%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20significant%20that%20both%20the%20PM%20and%20the%20Foreign%20Minister%20have%20raised%20concerns%20regarding%20China.%20Unfolding%20geopolitical%20events%20and%20their%20critical%20impact%20on%20trade%20and%20business%20vis-a-vis%20China%20in%20the%20past%20years%20have%20compelled%20this%20stance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20observed%20universally%20that%20China%2C%20led%20by%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20since%202013%2C%20has%20shown%20complete%20disregard%20for%20international%20norms%3B%20an%20example%20being%20the%20protracted%20stand-off%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20Sikkim%20or%20Arunachal%20Pradesh.%20China%20has%20been%20muscling%20its%20way%20into%20other%20neighbours%20like%20Vietnam%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%20as%20well%2C%20provoking%20strong%20protests%20and%20strategic%20re-alliance%20among%20these%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20engaged%20India%20in%20border%20standoffs%20and%20a%20proxy%20war%20to%20further%20its%20policy%20of%20expansion.%20As%20China%20grew%20into%20a%20mighty%20economic%20and%20military%20power%2C%20what%20came%20to%20the%20fore%20was%20its%20insolence%20towards%20the%20rules-based%20international%20order%20and%20a%20shared%20commitment%20to%20conduct%20international%20affairs%20in%20accordance%20with%20laws%2C%20principles%20and%20practices%20embodied%20in%20institutions%20such%20as%20the%20United%20Nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20continues%20to%20flout%20regional%20security%20arrangements%2C%20trade%20agreements%20and%20multilateral%20financial%20institutions%20at%20every%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20always%20believed%20that%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20region%20are%20better%20served%20through%20a%20balance%20of%20forces%20rather%20than%20the%20dominance%20of%20any%20single%20force%20-%20whether%20it%20is%20the%20Americans%20or%20the%20Chinese.%20This%20is%20one%20of%20the%20pillars%20of%20India's%20Indo-Pacific%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20has%20been%20travelling%20the%20world%20listening%20to%20the%20problems%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%20(Global%20South%20refers%20to%20countries%20in%20Africa%2C%20Asia%2C%20and%20Latin%20America%2C%20which%20are%20developing%2C%20less%20developed%2C%20or%20underdeveloped.%20These%20countries%20have%20higher%20levels%20of%20poverty%2C%20income%20inequality%2C%20and%20challenging%20living%20conditions%20compared%20to%20the%20wealthier%20nations%20of%20the%20Global%20North).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeveloping%20nations%20have%20always%20struggled%20to%20find%20a%20common%20agenda.%20Countries%20come%20together%20for%20a%20short-term%20goal%20or%20agenda%20but%20are%20rarely%20willing%20to%20coordinate%20and%20cooperate%20over%20the%20long%20term.%20India%20in%20its%20G20%20presidency%20has%20gone%20all%20out%20to%20bring%20a%20perceptible%20change%20in%20international%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PM%20and%20Foreign%20Minister%20also%20raised%20supply%20chain%20worries%20and%20called%20for%20a%20more%20balanced%20approach%20to%20doing%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESupply%20chain%20problems%20emerged%20during%20Covid%20lockdowns%20due%20to%20shifts%20in%20demand%2C%20labour%20shortages%20and%20structural%20factors.%20For%20India%2C%20the%20pressure%20was%20felt%20when%20raw%20material%20imports%20from%20China%20were%20stopped.%20From%20wooden%20furniture%20to%20nacelle%20and%20blade%20of%20wind%20turbines%20to%20cells%20of%20solar%20panel%20modules%2C%20India%20has%20been%20dependent%20on%20China%20for%20the%20supply%20of%20huge%20volumes%20of%20raw%20materials%2C%20which%20was%20impacted%20by%20the%20disruptions%20due%20to%20Covid.%20The%20delay%20in%20procuring%20these%20raw%20materials%20from%20alternate%20sources%20had%20a%20multiplier%20effect%2C%20resulting%20in%20project%20delays%20and%20the%20rise%20in%20prices%20of%20the%20finished%20products%20in%20India.%20The%20continued%20ramifications%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20have%20exacerbated%20the%20global%20divide%20of%20access%20to%20resources.%20Countries%20in%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20India%20included%2C%20have%20been%20at%20the%20receiving%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina's%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI)%20has%20often%20been%20seen%20as%20a%20project%20focused%20on%20benefits%20to%20China%20and%20not%20the%20countries%20that%20have%20provided%20access%20and%20infrastructure%20to%20build%20the%20road.%20The%20debt%20trap%20that%20many%20African%20nations%20have%20fallen%20into%20is%20for%20the%20entire%20world%20to%20see.%20The%20cost%20of%20capital%20has%20been%20so%20high%20that%20the%20debt%20trap%20seems%20perpetual.%20Pakistan%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20Zambia%2C%20Kenya%2C%20Laos%2C%20Mongolia%20to%20name%20a%20few%2C%20are%20the%20most%20indebted%20nations%20to%20China.%20In%20these%20countries%2C%20there%20are%20no%20jobs%20and%20inflation%20is%20skyrocketing%2C%20leading%20to%20waves%20of%20loan%20defaults%20and%20political%20unrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agile%20response%20of%20China%20in%20anticipating%20and%20acquiring%20metals%20that%20will%20strengthen%20the%20industries%20of%20the%20future%20has%20already%20begun%20shaking%20up%20the%20powerful%20West.%20The%20Global%20South%20can't%20even%20comprehend%20the%20impending%20damage.%20China%20has%20been%20encouraging%20the%20use%20of%20its%20currency%20internationally%2C%20including%20in%20Brazil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvolving%20geopolitical%20factors%20are%20now%20causing%20new%20risks%20and%20pockets%20of%20stress.%20Affected%20sectors%20include%20metals%20and%20mining%2C%20chemicals%2C%20automotives%2C%20semiconductors%20and%20technology.%20China%20continues%20to%20secure%20its%20raw%20material%20supplies%20by%20buying%2023%20equity%20stakes%20in%20lithium%2C%20nickel%20and%20cobalt%20companies.%20China%20has%20bought%20half%20of%20the%20world's%20biggest%20lithium%20mines%20put%20on%20the%20market%20since%202018.%20This%20has%20given%20China%20an%20edge%20over%20the%20global%20battery%20metal%20supply%20chain.%20PM%20Modi%20is%20cautioning%20against%20this%20new%20model%20of%20colonialism%20when%20he%20says%20those%20who%20have%20the%20rare%20critical%20metals%20have%20the%20global%20responsibility%20for%20inclusive%20growth%20of%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Global%20North%20too%20has%20not%20helped%20matters.%20According%20to%20reports%2C%20%26quot%3Bfriend-shoring%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20post%20Covid%20era%20since%20late%202022%2C%20in%20which%20bilateral%20trade%20benefits%20the%20countries%20that%20share%20similar%20political%20and%20economic%20orientation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20recent%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20Johannesburg%2C%20there%20was%20no%20consensus%20between%20India%20and%20China%20on%20the%20expansion%20of%20the%20group.%20India's%20approach%20to%20promote%20cooperation%20among%20developing%20countries%20and%20engagement%20with%20the%20G7%20is%20opposed%20by%20China%2C%20which%20wants%20countries%20inclined%20towards%20its%20policies%20and%20part%20of%20its%20BRI%20initiative%20to%20join%20the%20bloc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20episodic%20'tug-of-war'%20will%20continue.%20India%2C%20of%20late%2C%20has%20given%20up%20its%20decade-old%20stand%20of%20not%20being%20on%20the%20offensive%20on%20global%20forums.%20It%20is%20now%20showing%20signs%20of%20resistance%20and%20building%20allies%20across%20the%20globe%20to%20suit%20its%20internal%20needs.%20But%20it%20needs%20more%20allies%20to%20come%20out%20in%20the%20open%20and%20challenge%20China's%20hegemony%20in%20the%20economic%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693230720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fkue9s8no_pm-modi-1200_625x300_28_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdecoding-pm-modis-remarks-on-china-and-supply-chain-worries-4336857%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20has%20been%20dependent%20on%20China%20for%20the%20supply%20of%20huge%20volumes%20of%20raw%20materials%2C%20which%20was%20impacted%20by%20the%20disruptions%20due%20to%20Covid.%20The%20delay%20in%20procuring%20these%20raw%20materials%20from%20alternate%20sources%20had%20a%20multiplier%20effect.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fdecoding-pm-modis-remarks-on-china-and-supply-chain-worries-4336857%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bengaluru%20Auto%20Driver's%20Back-To-School%20Story%20Is%20Viral%