%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28145954%2F1-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28145954%2F1-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28145954%2F1-1-300x265.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28145954%2F1-1-1024x904.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670220%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221059%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExpenditure%20limit%20for%20a%20candidate%20in%20elections%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%206%2C%202022%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20issued%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feci.gov.in%2Ffiles%2Ffile%2F13928-limits-of-candidate%25E2%2580%2599s-expenses-enhanced%2F%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20stating%20that%20the%20spending%20limit%20for%20candidates%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20elections%20had%20been%20increased.%20The%20expenditure%20ceiling%20varied%20from%20state%20to%20state.%20For%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20in%20states%20where%20the%20cap%20for%20individual%20candidates%20was%20Rs%2070%20lakh%2C%20the%20amount%20was%20increased%20to%20Rs%2095%20lakh.%20Similarly%2C%20in%20the%20states%20where%20the%20limit%20was%20Rs%2054%20lakh%2C%20it%20was%20increased%20to%20Rs%2075%20lakh.%20In%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20states%20where%20the%20spending%20limit%20for%20a%20candidate%20during%20the%20election%20period%20was%20Rs%2028%20lakh%2C%20the%20amount%20was%20increased%20to%20Rs%2040%20lakh.%20Finally%2C%20in%20states%20where%20the%20spending%20limit%20for%20an%20MLA%20candidate%20was%20Rs%2020%20lakh%2C%20it%20was%20raised%20to%20Rs%2028%20lakh.%20According%20to%20this%20press%20release%2C%20the%20expenditure%20limit%20by%20any%20candidate%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%20of%20Gujarat%20was%20capped%20at%20Rs%2040%20lakh.%3C%2Fp