0the%20guiding%20principles%20to%20distinguish%20between%20the%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20the%20political%20party%20and%20the%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20the%20candidates%20was%20enunciated%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EKanwar%20Lal%20Gupta%20vs%20Amar%20Nath%20Chawla%3C%2Fem%3E%20(AIR%201975%20SC%20308)%20case%2C%20wherein%20the%20apex%20court%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20political%20party%20sponsoring%20a%20candidate%20incurs%20expenditure%20in%20connection%20with%20his%20election%20as%20distinguished%20from%20expenditure%20on%20general%20party%20propaganda%2C%20and%20the%20candidate%20knowingly%20takes%20advantage%20of%20it%20and%20participates%20in%20the%20programme%20or%20activity%20and%20fails%20to%20disavow%20the%20expenditure%20or%20consents%20to%20it%20or%20acquiesce%20in%20it%2C%20it%20would%20be%20reasonable%20to%20infer%2C%20say%20in%20special%20circumstances%2C%20that%20he%20authorized%20the%20political%20party%20to%20incur%20such%20expenditure%20and%20he%20cannot%20escape%20the%20rigours%20of%20the%20ceiling%20by%20saying%20that%20he%20has%20not%20incurred%20the%20expense%2C%20but%20his%20political%20party%20has%20done%20so.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153243%2F6-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153243%2F6-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153243%2F6-1-300x184.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153243%2F6-1-1024x626.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670234%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22734%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPage%20204%20of%20the%20Compendium%20mentions%20that%20as%20per%20Section%2077%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%2C%20the%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20a%20political%20party%20on%20advertisements%20in%20connection%20with%20any%20election%20can%20be%20categorised%20into%20three%20classifications%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(i)%20Expenditure%20on%20general%20party%20propaganda%20seeking%20support%20for%20the%20party%20and%20its%20candidates%20in%20general%2C%20but%20without%20reference%20to%20any%20particular%20candidate%20or%20any%20particular%20class%2Fgroup%20of%20candidates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(ii)%20Expenditure%20incurred%20by%20the%20party%20in%20advertisements%20etc.%20directly%20supporting%20and%2For%20vote%20for%20a%20particular%20candidate%20or%20group%20of%20candidates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(iii)%20Expenditure%20incurred%20by%20the%20party%20which%20can%20be%20related%20to%20the%20expenditure%20for%20promoting%20the%20prospects%20of%20any%20particular%20candidate%20or%20group%20of%20candidates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApplying%20the%20ratio%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20landmark%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EKanwarlal%20Gupta%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20clarified%20that%20in%20the%20case%20of%20any%20advertisement%20by%20political%20parties%2C%20whether%20in%20print%20or%20electronic%20or%20any%20other%20media%2C%20falling%20in%20category%20(i)%20above%2C%20which%20is%20not%20relatable%20to%20the%20election%20of%20a%20particular%20candidate%20or%20a%20group%20of%20candidates%2C%20the%20expenditure%20may%20be%20treated%20as%20expenditure%20on%20general%20party%20propaganda%20of%20the%20political%20party.%20In%20cases%20of%20expenditure%20falling%20in%20categories%20(ii)%20and%20(iii)%20above%20which%20is%20relatable%20to%20a%20particular%20candidate%20or%20group%20of%20candidates%2C%20the%20expenditure%20shall%20be%20treated%20as%20expenditure%20authorized%20by%20the%20candidates%20concerned%20and%20such%20expenditure%20shall%20be%20accounted%20for%20in%20the%20election%20expenditure%20of%20the%20said%20candidates.%20In%20cases%20where%20expenditure%20is%20incurred%20by%20the%20party%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20given%20group%20of%20candidates%2C%20the%20expenditure%20shall%20be%20divided%20equally%20among%20the%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153330%2F7-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153330%2F7-1.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153330%2F7-1-300x215.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153330%2F7-1-1024x733.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670235%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22859%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EViolation%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20%E2%80%98Narendra%20Bhupendra%20%E2%80%93%20%E0%AA%A8%E0%AA%B0%E0%AB%87%E0%AA%A8%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%A6%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%B0%20%E0%AA%AD%E0%AB%82%E0%AA%AA%E0%AB%87%E0%AA%A8%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%A6%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%B0%E2%80%99%20Facebook%20page%20was%20associated%20with%20the%20BJP%2C%20named%20after%20Bhupendra%20Patel%20and%20the%20page%E2%80%99s%20advertisements%20also%20used%20his%20photo%2C%20it%20would%20fall%20under%20the%20second%20or%20third%20category%20of%20guiding%20principles%20laid%20down%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKanwar%20Lal%20Gupta%20vs%20Amarnath%20Chawla%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment%20to%20differentiate%20between%20election%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20a%20political%20party%20and%20election%20expenditure%20incurred%20by%20candidates%2C%20depending%20on%20interpretation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPage%20204%20of%20the%20Compendium%20of%20Instructions%20on%20Monitoring%20of%20Election%20Expenditure%20published%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20mentions%20that%20in%20the%20cases%20of%20expenditure%20falling%20into%20the%20second%20and%20third%20category%2C%20which%20is%20relatable%20to%20a%20particular%20candidate%20or%20group%20of%20candidates%2C%20the%20expenditure%20shall%20be%20treated%20as%20expenditure%20authorized%20by%20the%20candidate%20concerned%20and%20such%20expenditure%20shall%20be%20accounted%20for%20in%20the%20election%20expenditure%20of%20the%20said%20candidate%20or%20group%20of%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhupendra%20Patel%2C%20the%20candidate%20from%20the%20Ghatlodia%20assembly%20constituency%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20furnished%20the%20amount%20of%20Rs%2030%2C15%2C000%20as%20the%20total%20election%20fund%20and%20a%20total%20expenditure%20of%20Rs%2018%2C74%2C049.%20He%20has%20not%20included%20the%20cost%20of%20advertisement%20run%20on%20social%20media%20in%20his%20election%20expenditure.%20Whereas%20after%20nomination%2C%20the%20amount%20spent%20for%20advertisement%20by%20the%20Facebook%20page%20%E2%80%98Narendra%20Bhupendra%20%E2%80%93%20%E0%AA%A8%E0%AA%B0%E0%AB%87%E0%AA%A8%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%A6%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%B0%20%E0%AA%AD%E0%AB%82%E0%AA%AA%E0%AB%87%E0%AA%A8%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%A6%E0%AB%8D%E0%AA%B0%E2%80%99%20named%20after%20Bhupendra%20Patel%20and%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20between%20Rs%2038%2C62%2C694%20and%20Rs%2031%2C47%2C600.%20These%20expenses%20have%20not%20been%20included%20in%20the%20election%20expenditure%20filed%20by%20Bhupendra%20Patel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Silence%20Period%E2%80%99%20Rule%20vis-a-vis%20Election%20Campaigning%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feci.gov.in%2Ffiles%2Ffile%2F9433-provisions-of-section-126-of-the-representation-of-the-people-act-1951-reg%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSection%2520126%2520of%2520the%2520RP%2Cof%2520television%2520and%2520similar%2520apparatus.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESection%20126%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Representation%20of%20the%20People%20Act%2C%201951%2C%20no%20person%20shall%20display%20any%20election%20matter%20to%20the%20public%20through%20cinematography%2C%20television%20or%20other%20similar%20means%20during%20the%20period%20of%2048%20hours%20ending%20with%20the%20hours%20fixed%20for%20the%20conclusion%20of%20polling%20for%20any%20election%20in%20any%20polling%20constituency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20issued%20a%20press%20release%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D1873396%5C%22%3ENovember%203%2C%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20regarding%20the%20Gujarat%20assembly%20elections.%20In%20the%2018th%20point%20of%20this%20press%20release%2C%20an%20advisory%20was%20issued%20to%20political%20parties%20for%20the%20silence%20period.%20It%20clearly%20stated%20that%20this%20was%20done%20in%20view%20of%20the%20advancements%20in%20communication%20technology%20and%20the%20increasing%20use%20of%20social%20media%20under%20the%20provision%20of%20Section%20126%20of%20the%20RP%20Act%2C%201951.%20It%20states%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20multi-phased%20election%2C%20the%20silence%20period%20of%20the%20last%2048%20hours%20may%20be%20on%20in%20certain%20constituencies%20while%20campaigning%20is%20ongoing%20in%20other%20constituencies.%20In%20such%20an%20event%2C%20there%20should%20not%20be%20any%20direct%20or%20indirect%20reference%20amounting%20to%20soliciting%20support%20for%20parties%20or%20candidates%20in%20the%20constituencies%20observing%20the%20silence%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20silence%20period%2C%20star%20campaigners%20and%20other%20political%20leaders%20should%20refrain%20from%20addressing%20the%20media%20by%20way%20of%20press%20conferences%20and%20giving%20interviews%20on%20election%20matters.%20The%20point%20worth%20noting%20is%20that%20the%20assemb