ns%20about%20his%20ability%20to%20continue%20as%20president.%20Trump%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20been%20indicted%20in%20four%20cases%20featuring%2091%20total%20criminal%20counts%20and%20elicits%20words%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Ccorrupt%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Ccrooked%E2%80%9D%20(named%20by%2015%25)%2C%20along%20with%20%E2%80%9Cbad%E2%80%9D%20and%20other%20generally%20negative%20comments%20(11%25).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fbiden-is-old-trump-is-corrupt-ap-norc-poll-has-ominous-signs-for-both-in-possible-2024-rematch%2Farticleshow%2F103136602.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fbiden-is-old-trump-is-corrupt-ap-norc-poll-has-ominous-signs-for-both-in-possible-2024-rematch%2Famp_articleshow%2F103136602.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fbiden-is-old-trump-is-corrupt-ap-norc-poll-has-ominous-signs-for-both-in-possible-2024-rematch%2Famp_articleshow%2F103136602.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Legacy%20of%20Des%20Raj%20Kali%2C%20Renowned%20Writer%2C%20Journalist%20and%20Literature%20Icon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153910%2Fimage-1260-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJalandhar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Noted%20Punjabi%20writer%2C%20journalist%2C%20critic%20and%20social%20thinker%2C%20Des%20Raj%20Kali%2C%20who%20took%20literature%20from%20the%20roots%20of%20lesser-known%20villages%20of%20Punjab%20to%20the%20global%20stage%2C%20passed%20away%20on%20August%2027%20in%20Chandigarh.%20He%20was%2051.%20He%20was%20suffering%20from%20liver%20cirrhosis%20and%20was%20admitted%20to%20Chandigarh%E2%80%99s%20PGI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20cremation%20will%20take%20place%20on%20August%2029.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKali%20is%20survived%20by%20his%20wife%20and%20three%20children%20%E2%80%93%20a%20son%2C%20Karan%2C%20and%20two%20daughters%2C%20Shivalika%20and%20Zunish.%20He%20hailed%20from%20Mithapur%20village%20in%20Jalandhar%2C%20which%20is%20also%20famous%20for%20hockey%20stars%20from%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKali%20wrote%20about%20Dalit%20life%20and%20injustices%20face%20through%20his%20own%20experiences%20of%20the%20society%20that%20he%20grew%20up%20in.%20The%20author%20would%20often%20say%20that%20he%20could%20withstand%20the%20adversities%20of%20life%20as%20he%20came%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98culturally%20elite%20Dalit%20background%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHailing%20from%20the%20Dalit%20heartland%20of%20Punjab%2C%20the%20Doaba%20region%2C%20Kali%E2%80%99s%20work%20was%20influenced%20by%20the%20teachings%20of%20Sufi%20saints%20who%20thronged%20the%20villages%20and%20deserts%20of%20undivided%20rural%20Punjab%2C%20and%20iconic%20Dalit%20writers%20Lal%20Singh%20Dil%20and%20Sant%20Gulab%20Das.%20The%20originality%20in%20his%20work%20brought%20a%20new%20turn%20in%20Punjabi%20story%20writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKali%20explored%20anti-caste%20struggles%2C%20culture%2C%20tradition%20and%20literature%20in%20the%20form%20of%20novels%20and%20short%20stories.%20He%20also%20presented%20research%20papers%20in%20renowned%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20journalist%20Pal%20Singh%20Nauli%2C%20who%20knew%20Kali%20for%20over%2030%20years%2C%20shared%20some%20lesser-known%20facts%20about%20the%20writer%E2%80%99s%20life%2C%20which%20had%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20him.%20%E2%80%9CKali%20grew%20up%20in%20an%20environment%20where%20all%20that%20he%20saw%20was%20an%20unjust%20society%2C%20where%20Dalits%20were%20meant%20to%20perform%20menial%20jobs%20only.%20His%20father%20used%20to%20pick%20the%20dead%20animals%20on%20his%20bicycle%20in%20the%20village%20and%20skin%20them.%20Even%20as%20a%20child%2C%20Kali%20used%20to%20accompany%20his%20father%20to%20this%20work.%20He%20would%20often%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EAsi%20sadiyan%20to%20uppercaste%20loka%20di%20gulami%20karde%20a%20rahe%20a%2C%20asi%20es%20baare%20kyu%20na%20gal%20kariye%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%20(We%20have%20been%20the%20slaves%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98upper%E2%80%99%20caste%20people.%20Why%20should%20we%20not%20talk%20about%20this%3F)'%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20words%20of%20one%20of%20his%20close%20friends%2C%20Makhan%20Mann%2C%20a%20retired%20Punjab%20revenue%20officer%20who%20also%20took%20to%20writing%2C%20Kali%20knew%20how%20to%20read%20a%20book.%20%E2%80%9COur%20friendship%20is%2035%20years%20old.%20Kali%20used%20to%20address%20me%20as%20Mann%20Bhaji.%20We%20used%20to%20write%20stories%20together.%20It%20was%20his%20heart%20of%20gold%2C%20like%20a%20fakir%3Cem%3E%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20which%20earned%20him%20love%20and%20respect%20from%20people.%20He%20was%20a%20writer%2C%20poet%2C%20journalist%2C%20historian%2C%20critic%2C%20philosopher%20and%20a%20wonderful%20human%20being.%20%3Cem%3EOh%20Daler%20si%3C%2Fem%3E%20(He%20was%20a%20fearless%20person).%20He%20never%20took%20caste%20as%20a%20caste.%20He%20would%20rather%20talk%20about%20the%20problem%20and%20maintain%20a%20scientific%20approach%20to%20it.%20He%20used%20to%20study%20deeply%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKali%E2%80%99s%20writings%20and%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMann%20shared%20how%20Kali%E2%80%99s%20novel%20%3Cem%3EShanti%20Parav%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20by%20Orient%20Blackswan%2C%20remained%20one%20of%20his%20bestselling%20books.%20The%20book%20is%20based%20on%20post-colonial%20Punjab%20from%20a%20Dalit%20person%E2%80%99s%20perspective.%20It%20talked%20about%20governance%2C%20violence%20and%20peace%20through%20three%20retired%20Dalit%20characters.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20days%2C%20he%20was%20writing%20a%20novel%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EDukh%20Kade%20Budhe%20nai%20Hunde%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Sorrow%20never%20gets%20old).%20He%20was%20also%20planning%20to%20start%20a%20fortnightly%20newspaper%20but%20we%20never%20knew%20that%20he%20would%20leave%20us%20so%20all%20of%20sudden%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKali%E2%80%99s%20short%20story%20collections%20include%20%3Cem%3EKath%20Kali%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Stories%20of%20Kali)%2C%20%3Cem%3EFakiri%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Mendicancy)%20and%20%3Cem%3EYahan%20Chai%20Achi%20Nahi%20Banti%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Good%20Tea%20is%20Not%20Served%20Here).%20His%20novels%20are%20%3Cem%3EAntheen%20%3C%2Fem%3E(Eternal)%2C%20%3Cem%3EPrathan%20Pauran%3C%2Fem%3E%20(First%20Puran)%2C%20%3Cem%3EShanti%20Parav%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EShehar%20Vich%20Sahn%20Honn%20da%20Matlab%3C%2Fem%3E%20(What%20it%20Means%20to%20be%20a%20Bull%20in%20the%20Town).%20He%20also%20published%20research%20papers%20on%20the%20literature%20and%20culture%20of%20Punjab%20and%20gender%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20research%20on%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Ghadar%20movement%20in%20the%20form%20of%20four%20books%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3EUngauley%20Nayak%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Forgotten%20Heroes)%2C%20%3Cem%3EGadri%20Banta%20Singh%20Sanghwal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EGadri%20Bhai%20Randhir%20Singh%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%3Cem%3E%20Gadri%20Ram%20Saran%20Dass%20Talwar%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20remains%20the%20best%20collection%20of%20historic%20work%20in%20Ghadar%20literature.%20Kali%20was%20associated%20with%20the%20Desh%20Bhagat%20Yadgaar%20Committee%2C%20Jalandhar%2C%20a%20platform%20dedicated%20to%20the%20Ghadar%20movement%2C%20and%20was%20often%20spotted%20at%20the%20committee%20office%20sharing%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%20with%20like-minded%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKali%E2%80%99s%20work%20was%20celebrated%20in%20major%20festivals%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20including%20the%20prestigious%20Jaipur%20Literature%20Festival%2C%20Samanvay%20Samagam%20and%20at%20renowned%20foreign%20universities.%20The%20writer%20had%20the%20honour%20of%20presenting%20his%20work%20at%20Monash%20University%2C%20Melbourne%20on%20the%20125th%20birth%20anniversary%20of%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20to%20trace%20common%20ground%20between%20the%20people%20from%20the%20Dalit%20and%20Australian%20tribal%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20novel%20%3Cem%3EShanti%20Parav%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20celebrated%20at%20the%20Chandigarh%20Literature%20Festival%20in%202013.%20He%20also%20edited%20the%20literary%20quarterly%20%3Cem%3ELakeer%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20directed%20a%20documentary%20%3Cem%3EKitey%20Mil%20Ve%20Mahi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20going%20to%20the%20Jaipur%20Literature%20Fest%20in%202016%2C%20Kali%2C%20while%20talking%20about%20the%20history%20of%20Dalit%20literature%20and%20its%20writers%2C%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CDalit%20and%20Punjabi%20literature%20have%20their%20roots%20in%20the%20Buddhist%20and%20Sufi%20philosophy%20with%20genesis%20through%20%E2%80%98Nath%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Yogis%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20Punjabi%20culture.%20While%20Dalit%20literature%20was%20philosophical%2C%20the%20Hindi%20and%20the%20Marathi%20writers%20like%20Jyoti%20Rao%20Phule%20and%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20were%20politically%20influenced.%20That%20is%20why%20I%20would%20talk%20about%20iconic%20Dalit%20writers%20like%20Gulab%20Dass%2C%20Peero%20Preman%2C%20Wazir%20Singh%20and%20Nurung%20Devi.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20would%20also%20share%20that%20the%20folk%20and%20oral%20Punjabi%20literature%20that%20he%20learnt%20through%20his%20ancestors%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20his%20writings.%20Kali%20also%20remained%20associated%20with%20All%20India%20Radio%20(AIR)%20in%20Jalandhar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20award-winning%20author%20started%20his%20career%20by%20working%20for%20Punjabi%20newspapers%20%3Cem%3ENawan%20Zamana%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EDesh%20Sewak.%3C%2Fem%3E%20He%20was%20the%20resident%20editor%20of%20the%20magazine%20section%20of%20%3Cem%3EDainik%20Bhaskar%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20Jalandhar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost%20COVID-19%2C%20Kali%20was%20running%20his%20own%20YouTube%20channel%20%3Cem%3EBarqtanWebTV%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20platform%20where%20he%20discussed%20caste%20issues%2C%20culture%2C%20tradition%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Punjabi%20and%20Punjabiyat%20and%20human-interest%20issues.%20He%20described%20his%20channel%20as%20%E2%80%98Dua%E2%80%99%20and%20would%20share%20his%20web%20channel%20videos%20with%20his%20friends%2C%20journalists%20and%20like-minded%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20vocal%20against%20atrocities%20on%20the%20people%20from%20the%20minority%20communities%20and%20the%20Adivasis.%20Recently%2C%20when%20the%20video%20of%20a%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20leader%20urinating%20on%20the%20face%20of%20an%20Adivasi%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20went%20viral%2C%20Kali%20held%20a%20special%20programme%2C%20holding%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20the%20right-wing%20groups%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKali%E2%80%99s%20personal%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20leader%20Rajesh%20Bagha%2C%20who%20was%20Kali%E2%80%99s%20close%20friend%2C%20shared%20some%20interesting%20facts%20about%20his%20personal%20life.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20many%20people%20know%20that%20Kali%20had%20an%20inter-caste%20but%20arranged%20marriage.%20His%20wife%20was%20a%20Brahmin.%20It%20was%20because%20of%20Kali%E2%80%99s%20nature%20that%20his%20father-in-law%20decided%20to%20approach%20his%20family%20for%20marriage.%20He%20was%20energetic%2C%20a%20carefree%20person%20and%20someone%20who%20would%20deeply%20feel%20for%20his%20friends.%20It%20is%20a%20huge%20loss%20for%20us%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBagha%20said%20Kali%20was%20well-read.%20He%20would%20delve%20deep%20into%20his%20characters.%20%E2%80%9CKali%20used%20to%20live%20in%20his%20characters.%20Often%20when%20we%20met%20over%20a%20cup%20of%20tea%2C%20we%20would%20notice%20him%20deeply%20lost%20in%20his%20thoughts.%20He%20would%20share%20that%20I%20am%20writing%20a%20story%20and%20the%20character%20was%20living%20with%20him%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20friend%20Imran%20Khan%2C%20who%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%2C%20was%20so%20much%20influenced%20by%20Kali%E2%80%99s%20work%20that%20after%20reading%20one%20of%20his%20pieces%20in%20%3Cem%3EDainik%20Bhaskar%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%202010%2C%20he%20went%20to%20meet%20him.%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20how%20I%20got%20a%20friend%20and%20a%20philosopher%20for%20life.%20Kali%E2%80%99s%20office%20near%20Jalandhar%20Doordarshan%20Kendra%20remained%20our%20sought-after%20destination%2C%20where%20our%20conversations%20ranged%20from%20life%2C%20society%2C%20politics%2C%20national%20and%20international%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20shared%20that%20apart%20from%20his%20writings%2C%20Kali%20was%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20rising%20communal%20hatred%20and%20attacks%20on%20the%20minorities%2C%20particularly%20Muslims.%20%E2%80%9CRecently%2C%20when%20communal%20tensions%20flared%20up%20in%20Nuh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Kali%20pointed%20out%20that%20this%20was%20yet%20another%20attempt%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20divert%20people%E2%80%99s%20attention%20from%20the%20incident%20in%20Manipur.%20He%20would%20feel%20the%20miseries%20of%20the%20minorities%20and%20often%20convey%20perturbed%20thoughts%20about%20the%20same.%20In%20him%2C%20we%20have%20lost%20a%20fine%20journalist%2C%20thinker%2C%20writer%2C%20and%20a%20friend%20for%20life.%20That%20office%20and%20our%20evenings%20will%20never%20be%20the%20same%20again%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693220405000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28153910%2Fimage-1260-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-legacy-of-des-raj-kali-renowned-writer-journalist-and-literature-icon%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kali%20explored%20anti-caste%20struggles%2C%20culture%2C%20tradition%20and%20literature%20in%20the%20form%20of%20novels%20and%20short%20stories.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fthe-legacy-of-des-raj-kali-renowned-writer-journalist-and-l