3E%2C%C2%A0about%20the%20underpinning%20of%20the%20landscapes%20that%20she%20had%20earlier%20sketched%20so%20vividly.%20Not%20%E2%80%98deconstruction%E2%80%99%20research%2C%20but%20a%20narrative%20of%20how%20the%20British%20constructed%20secure%20enclaves%20adjacent%20to%20or%20separate%20from%20existing%20ones.%20Together%20with%20this%2C%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20officials%20conquered%20their%20ignorance%20of%20a%20country%20of%20which%20they%20had%20initially%20known%20only%20the%20ports%20%E2%80%93%20by%20collecting%2C%20speculating%20and%20recording.%20Llewellyn-Jones%E2%80%99%20half-century%20of%20felicity%20in%20Urdu%2C%20familiarity%20and%20empathy%20with%20the%20%3Cem%3Edramatis%20personae%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20sites%2C%20and%20the%20gift%20for%20linking%20individuals%2C%20ideas%2C%20plans%2C%20and%20geographies%20give%20a%20rich%20texture%20to%20this%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chapters%20are%20divided%20into%20two%20sections%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20from%201690%20(the%20founding%20of%20Calcutta)%20to%201790%20(when%20the%20three%20%E2%80%98Presidencies%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20were%20in%20place)%3B%20the%20second%2C%201790-1860%2C%20after%20which%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20territories%20were%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20British%20Crown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20353px)%2085vw%2C%20353px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28130545%2F71QDyRMTZ7L.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22353%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28130545%2F71QDyRMTZ7L.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28130545%2F71QDyRMTZ7L-200x300.jpg%20200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F28130545%2F71QDyRMTZ7L-683x1024.jpg%20683w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670174%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERosie%20Llewellyn-Jones%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EEmpire%20Building%3A%20The%20Construction%20of%20British%20India%201690-1860%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EPenguin%20Random%20House%20India%20(January%202023)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stage%20is%20India%2C%20but%20the%20shadow%20of%20European%20developments%20is%20in%20the%20background%20%E2%80%93%20the%20first%20period%20was%20dominated%20by%20wars%2C%20from%20those%20of%20Louis%20XIV%20to%20those%20of%20Napoleon%3B%20these%20echoed%20in%20India%2C%20where%20British%20soldiers%20were%20confronting%20the%20French%2C%20and%20performing%20other%20tasks%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20mapping%20and%20categorising%2C%20putting%20together%20buildings%20for%20homes%20and%20offices.%20There%20was%20a%20curiosity%2C%20an%20eagerness%20to%20understand%20languages%20and%20the%20arts%2C%20and%20a%20readiness%20to%20mix%20socially%20with%20Indians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20period%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98war-free%E2%80%99%20decades%20in%20Europe%2C%20saw%20battles%20between%20the%20Company%20and%20%3Ci%3EIndian%3C%2Fi%3E%20rulers.%20In%20these%20years%2C%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20perceptions%20were%20influenced%20by%20the%20European%20%E2%80%98enlightenment%E2%80%99%2C%20when%20philosophers%20and%20political%20economists%20analysed%20social%20and%20political%20changes%2C%20and%20worked%20on%20theories%20to%20suggest%20reforms%20and%20institutions%20for%20the%20future.%20India%20was%20suggested%20as%20a%20convenient%20testing%20ground%20for%20some%20of%20these%20proposed%20institutions%2C%20as%20was%20described%20by%20Professor%20Eric%20Stokes%20in%201959%2C%20in%20his%20classic%20%3Ci%3EThe%20English%20Utilitarians%20and%20India%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStokes%E2%80%99%20pioneering%20work%20was%20followed%20after%20a%20decade%20by%20young%20scholars%20of%20South%20Asian%20history%20%E2%80%93%20at%20Indian%2C%20British%2C%20European%2C%20American%20and%20Australian%20universities.%20They%20shifted%20the%20focus%20from%20research%20on%20political%20conquests%20of%20%3Ci%3Ekingdoms%20%3C%2Fi%3Eto%20studies%20of%C2%A0the%20conquest%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3Epeople%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fi%3E%20the%20twin%20developments%20of%20a%20public%20works%20system%20and%20the%20codification%20of%20%E2%80%98law%20and%20order%E2%80%99%20embodied%20in%20civic%20and%20police%20administration.%20For%20these%20themes%2C%20there%20is%20copious%20primary%20material%20%E2%80%93%20one%2C%20buildings%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20still%20standing%2C%20and%20two%2C%20records%20stacked%20on%20miles%20of%20shelves%20in%20innumerable%20archives%20in%20India%20and%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20have%20been%20mined%20for%20the%20last%20four%20decades%2C%20beginning%20with%20Jan%20Morris%E2%80%99s%20%3Ci%3EStones%20of%20Empire%2C%3C%2Fi%3E%201983%2C%20and%20Llewellyn-Jones%E2%80%99%20own%C2%A0%3Ci%3EA%20Fatal%20Friendship%3A%20The%20Nawabs%2C%20the%20British%20and%20the%20City%20of%20Lucknow%2C%20%3C%2Fi%3E1985.%20As%20the%20East%20India%20Company%E2%80%99s%20political%20control%20extended%20over%20more%20regions%2C%20landscapes%2C%20urban%20and%20rural%2C%20became%20transformed%20%E2%80%93%20to%20older%20royal%20forts%20and%20palaces%2C%20cathedral%20%3Ci%3Emandirs%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20%3Ci%3Emasjid%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20ceremonial%20routes%2C%20were%20added%20%E2%80%98cities%20of%20palaces%E2%80%99%20(those%20of%20Company%20officials)%2C%20chequerboard%20cantonments%20(new%20versions%20of%20the%20%3Ci%3Echhaoni)%3C%2Fi%3E%2C%20simple%20but%20workable%20school%20buildings%20and%20civic%20offices%2C%20the%20use%20of%20chairs%20and%20tables%20which%20created%20a%20difference%20of%20height%20between%20the%20teacher%2Fofficial%20and%20the%20students%2Fsupplicants.%20Model%20institutions%20%E2%80%93%20hospitals%2C%20homes%20to%20contain%20the%20unwanted%20and%20the%20dangerous%20(lunatic%20asylums%20and%20jails)%2C%20metal%20bridges%20to%20ford%20rivers%20and%2C%20later%2C%20highways.%20supplemented%20with%20railway%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%2070%20years%20of%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20rule%20(from%20the%201790s)%2C%20military%20conquests%20continued%20but%20military%20engineers%20now%20doubled%20as%20civil%20engineers%20%E2%80%93%20until%20a%20separate%20cadre%20of%20civil%20engineers%20was%20established%2C%20and%20the%20Roorkee%20College%20was%20built%20in%201847.%20The%20fuzzy%20boundary%20between%20engineering%20and%20architecture%20in%20contemporary%20Britain%20was%20mirrored%20in%20the%20Company%20departments%2C%20where%20engineers%20proudly%20modified%20streets%20and%20buildings%2C%20with%20innovations%20like%20glass%20windows%20and%20clock%20towers.%20The%20last%2C%20a%20corollary%20of%20the%20English%20industrial%20revolution%2C%20was%20part%20of%20the%20totems%20of%20%E2%80%98improvement%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20buzzword%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20author%20suggests%20that%20while%20the%20initial%20sense%20of%20a%20meeting%20of%20the%20two%20cultures%20was%20invigorating%2C%20once%20success%20came%20easy%2C%20military%20and%20political%20victories%20took%20the%20edge%20off%20the%20initial%20curiosity%20about%20and%20respect%20for%20Indian%20knowledge%20systems%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%9C..the%20sense%20of%20wonder%20and%20enquiry%20exemplified%20by%20the%20Asiatick%20Society%20in%20its%20early%20days%20had%20been%20lost%20by%201800.%20As%20the%20new%20century%20dawned%2C%20Indians%20were%20increasingly%20seen%20as%20characters%20in%20an%20antique%20land%2C%20unchanging%20and%20unwilling%20to%20change.%20It%20was%20one%20of%20the%20Company%E2%80%99s%20most%20serious%20errors%20to%20underestimate%20the%20desire%20for%20progress%20among%20the%20people%20it%20ruled.%20Nor%20did%20it%20do%20much%20to%20exploit%20indigenous%20talent.%20It%20was%20also%20slow%20to%20recognise%20and%20adopt%20technological%20innovations%20from%20the%20West%20that%20were%20promoted%20by%20enterprising%20individuals%20in%20the%20face%20of%20indifference%20and%20penny-pinching.%20Yet%20somehow%20modern%20India%20was%20being%20constructed%2C%20%E2%80%A6in%20jerky%20and%20uneven%20steps%2C%20and%20often%20in%20greedy%20and%20self-serving%20ways%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20plea%20to%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20scholars%20on%20South%20Asian%20history%20%E2%80%93%20someone%20should%20write%20the%20sequel%20to%20this%20book.%201860-1950%20has%20been%20studied%20chiefly%20in%20terms%20of%20political%20debates%20and%20negotiations.%20Someone%20needs%20to%20pull%20together%20the%20research%20done%20on%20public%20works%2C%20both%20infrastructure%20and%20grand%20architecture%2C%C2%A0%20the%20development%20of%20school%20and%20university%20education%2C%20medical%20breakthroughs%2C%20linked%20to%20developments%20in%20the%20West%2C%20often%20anticipating%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20more%20important%2C%20historians%20should%20cross%20the%20%3Ci%3ELakshman%20Rekha%3C%2Fi%3E%20of%201947%20and%20point%20out%20continuities%20and%20breaks.%20We%20need%20to%20think%20about%20the%20rationale%20for%20the%20architectures%20of%20the%20last%2075%20years%2C%20class%20prejudices%20in%20town%20planning%2C%20and%20hierarchies%20in%20engineering%20projects.%20Another%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20the%20issues%20may%20be%20to%20puzzle%20out%20why%20a%20genius%20like%20Patrick%20Geddes%20has%20been%20ignored%20in%20the%20country%20where%20he%20did%20so%20much%20research%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20interacted%20with%20so%20many%20policy-makers%20and%20philosophers%2C%20and%20introduced%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%98civics%E2%80%99.%20What%20explains%20the%20class%20divide%20today%20between%20file-pushers%20and%20workers%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20in%20departments%20as%20different%20as%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20and%20in%20the%20CPWD%3F%C2%A0%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20description%20of%20modern%20dams%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20temples%20of%20modern%20India%E2%80%9D%20was%20evocative%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20should%20have%20been%20possible%20to%20use%20the%20same%20term%20for%20schools%2C%20hospitals%2C%20and%20civic%20centres.%20Citizens%20need%20to%20identify%20with%20their%20modern%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERosie%20Llewellyn-Jones%20should%20be%20read%20with%20attention%2C%20to%20get%20a%20sense%20of%20how%20negative%20perceptions%20can%20reduce%2C%20how%20empathy%20can%20enrich%2C%20how%20visual%20beauty%20can%20uplift%2C%20and%20how%20listlessness%20can%20destroy.%20It%20is%20a%20parable%20for%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fnarayani-gupta%5C%22%3ENarayani%20Gupta%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20historian.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693218624000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F06%2F5846239594_874090be6d_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-empire-building-rosie-llewellyn-jones%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rosie%20Llewellyn-Jones'%20Empire%20Building%3A%20The%20Construction%20of%20British%20India%201690-1860%20is%20not%20'deconstruction'%20research%2C%20but%20a%20narrative%20of%20how%20the%20British%20constructed%20secure%20enclaves%20adjacent%20to%20or%20separate%20from%20existing%20ones.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-empire-building-rosie-llewellyn-jones%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20U.S.%20Inches%20Closer%20To%20Breaking%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Monopoly%20On%20This%20Rare%20And%20Necessary%20Fuel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22The%20Putin%20government's%20control%20over%20a%20special%20nuclear%20fuel%20has%20rattled%20the%20West's%20atomic%20industry.%20New%20deals%20show%20the%20U.S.%20is%20finally%20trying%20to%20catch%20up.%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693218600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fimg.huffingtonpost.com%2Fasset%2F64ebc6bc250000390